    • Method Detail

      • addMarker

        @UiThread
public com.google.android.gms.maps.model.Marker addMarker(@NonNull
                                                                    com.google.android.gms.maps.GoogleMap map,
                                                                    com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng coordinates,
                                                                    int color)
        Adds a marker to the map. Note that this method does not save the marker to the marked object. It only adds it to the map, and returns the newly added marker.
        Parameters:
        map - The map to add the marker to.
        coordinates - The LatLng coordinates of the marker.
        color - The color of the marker. This will try to get the closest approximation to the color as there are a limited number of marker colors.
        Returns:
        The newly added marker.

      • removeMarker

        @UiThread
public void removeMarker()
        Removes the marker from the map, and sets it to null. This must be run on the UI thread.
